News24 Correspondent (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Witnesses to an attempted armed robbery in Lenasia shout out during a lethal shooting.WATCHJohannesburg - Three men were shot dead and three others injured in Brakpan, on the East Rand, when they were ambushed by another group of men who began shooting them indiscriminately, Gauteng police said on Sunday."Six men were seated at the side of a road next to a plastic recycling company in Brakpan," said Lieutenant Kay Makhubela about the incident which occurred on Saturday night."A group of people came up to them and without a word, started shooting."Three men died on the scene and three others, all in their 20s, were taken to hospital in critical condition."The motive is unknown."Makhubela said no arrests have yet been made and police were appealing to anyone with information about the crime to contact them.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.